      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COIN FLIP (3) put the writing on the wall when he showed strong pace early to be beaten only 0.8 lengths into second at this track and distance in 25.97. Finds the right race and with the aid of a low draw can go close. INDIAN CHIEF (7) produced a modest effort most recently when eighth at The Meadows over 525m behind Two Wheel Johnny (31.23) in a Maiden. Was in the money prior to that. The form out of last race has been strong. Great chance to atone. PAW MACHAMP (2) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fifth (22.65) in a Maiden at Ballarat. Has ability and can bounce back. INDY GLORIA (1) gets the right draw to be competitive.",
